description:
Animal Encounters is a new, exciting nature documentary series hosted by three friends: Gabi from Germany, Kezia from Kenya and Cassila from Brazil. Join these three adventurous women as they learn in the school of the out-doors, ride on elephants; touch cheetahs, play with monkeys, feed birds, get to know eels and learn to trust wolves. Feel their excitement as they dive with great white sharks, swim with turtles and spend a time observing wild meerkats in their natural environment. On this episode they visit an Elephant sanctuary where they ride elephants, hear the stories of these elephants and feed a baby elephant.  Visit www.animalencounters.tv
